reviews.review: The movie felt as though it didn’t have an adequate build up, and hardly a climax. It ended all too quickly. I don’t think there was any need for a second movie.

Best of this trilogy to me! I had lost hope, but this one brought bacj the nostalgia for me and I will see it again. 
(if you liked the Last Jedi, you will hate it)

I had to think about this one a while before writing a review. After a lot of thought, I think this one out-does it’s predecessor in just about every way. The character development through their growth and maturity feels real. And Kristoff wins MVP in my book for being the best example for both boys and girls of what a strong, supportive, loving partner should be.

Worst Disney film I've ever seen.
Poor story line,takes ages to get going,
Rubbish songs.
My 11 year old said she wouldn't watch it again even if it was on TV at home

An epic end to an amazing saga that completely makes up for eight. An absolute must watch and possibly one of the best star wars yet. So many twists you'll be on the edge of your seat the entire time!
Great sequel, the only thing not as good as the original is the music... still good but hard to top the original movie in that category!

best ending we could have possibly gotten . the first act of the movie was a little rough with some of the dialogue, but the 2nd and final acts of the movie were absolutely incredible. Rey is not a Mary Sue, she does have a bit more skill in TFA and TLJ than she should have, but people don't pay attention to why she has some of those fight skills (eg. always fighting with her staff and comparing the two in TLJ to learn quicker than most). it's very obvious that Kylo is much better than her at fighting, so the Mary Sue argument is bullshit. great character development and JJ always knows how to hit me in the feels.

I love elsa ,and i love all the scenes where she was. 
But i feel that kristoff is in this movie only to be love interest for ana
Enjoyable follow up that takes a Disney Princess story and makes it a tight Epic Journey film. Plenty of what you loved from the first film, with a dash of fantasy.
